				<text>19.2.2.4 Separation of Variables Ex2</text>
		</name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p class="HELM_exercise">Exercise</p>
<p>Solve the equation \(\dfrac{\mathrm{d}y}{\mathrm{d}x} = {@ff@}\) subject to the condition \(y(0) = 1\). Note: Type "log" or "ln" to represent the natural logarithm.</p>
<p>\(y =\) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]</p>]]></text>
		</questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p>We are given the equation \[ \dfrac{\mathrm{d}y}{\mathrm{d}x} = {@ff@}\]</p>
<p>Rearrange to obtain integrals on both sides \[\displaystyle\int {@%e^(bb*y)@}\ \mathrm{d}y = \displaystyle\int {@aa*x^(nn)@}\ \mathrm{d}x\]</p>
<p>Perform the integration and rearrange to find \(y\). \[\begin{aligned} {@1/(bb)*%e^(bb*y)@} &amp;= {@aa/(nn+1)*x^(nn+1)@} + C, \\ {@%e^(bb*y)@} &amp;= {@aa*bb/(nn+1)*x^(nn+1)@} + {@bb@}C, \\ {@bb*y@} &amp;= \log\left({@aa*bb/(nn+1)*x^(nn+1)@} + {@bb@}C\right),
    \\ y &amp;= {@1/bb@}\log\left({@aa*bb/(nn+1)*x^(nn+1)@} + {@bb@}C\right) \end{aligned}\]</p>

<p>We are given the condition \(y(0)=1\). Substituting \(x=0\) and setting the equation equal to \(1\) we may find \(C\). \[\begin{aligned} 1 &amp;= {@1/bb@}\log({@bb@}C), \\ \implies {@%e^bb@} &amp; = {@bb@}C, \\ \implies C &amp;= {@%e^(bb)/bb@} \end{aligned}\]</p>

<p>Then substituting \(C = {@%e^(bb)/bb@}\) into our general equation for \(y\) yields \[y = {@ta1@}\]</p>]]></text>
		</generalfeedback>
